# Commit Message Quick Reference

## Format Template
```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

<optional body>

<optional footer>
```

## Package Scopes
- `ui` - UI package changes
- `common` - Common package changes  
- `auth` - Auth package changes
- No scope - Affects all packages

## Release Triggering
- **Package name detection**: Include package name (`ui`, `auth`, `common`) in commit message to trigger release
- **Multiple packages**: Include multiple package names to release multiple packages
- **Manual release**: Use GitHub Actions workflow dispatch for manual releases

## Common Examples

### UI Package
```bash
feat(ui): add new Button component with variants
fix(ui): resolve modal backdrop click issue
docs(ui): update component usage examples
style(ui): improve button hover animations
```

### Common Package
```bash
feat(common): add createContext utility hook
fix(common): resolve type inference in fetch utility
refactor(common): optimize utility function performance
```

### Auth Package
```bash
feat(auth): add login with email/password
fix(auth): resolve session token expiration
perf(auth): optimize user context updates
```

### Root/General
```bash
chore: update dependencies to latest versions
docs: update project README with setup instructions
ci: fix GitHub Actions workflow configuration
```

### Multiple Packages
```bash
feat(ui, auth): add shared authentication components
fix(common): resolve utility and update ui package
docs(ui, common): update documentation for both packages
```

### Breaking Changes
```bash
feat(ui)!: change Button component API
fix(auth)!: update authentication flow
```

## Version Impact
- `feat` → Minor version bump
- `fix`, `perf`, `refactor`, `style`, `docs`, `chore` → Patch version bump
- `feat!`, `fix!` → Major version bump (breaking changes)